                            <comment id="12881461" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2010 23:51:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that fixes the issue and adds a unit test. I made it that if you go over the timeout from the client POV then it&apos;ll throw the Exception, else it will reset the scanner.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I had to up the timeout in the test, the other solution is to create a new unit test that would take longer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12881462" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2010 23:53:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is also in branch, same code that handles UnknownScannerException.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12881465" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2010 23:58:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Silly me, did a last minute cleanup that doesn&apos;t compile. New patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
